Sentencas: A binder system containing polyurethane precursors was used to in situ foam (direct foam) a (La0.6Sr0.4)(0.98) (Co-0.2 Fe-0.8) O3-delta (LSCF) composition for solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) cathode applications.
Titulo: In Situ Foaming of Porous (La0.6Sr0.4)0.98 (Co0.2 Fe0.8) O3-δ (LSCF) Cathodes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Applications

Sentencas: The relation between in situ foaming parameters on the final microstructure and electrochemical properties was characterized by microscopy and electrochemical impedance spectroscopy (EIS), respectively.
Titulo: In Situ Foaming of Porous (La0.6Sr0.4)0.98 (Co0.2 Fe0.8) O3-δ (LSCF) Cathodes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Applications

Sentencas: The optimal porous cathode architecture was formed with a 70 vol% solids loading within a polymer precursor composition with a volume ratio of 8:4:1 (isocyanate: PEG: surfactant) in a terpineol-based ink vehicle.
Titulo: In Situ Foaming of Porous (La0.6Sr0.4)0.98 (Co0.2 Fe0.8) O3-δ (LSCF) Cathodes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Applications

Sentencas: The resultant microstructure displayed a broad pore size distribution with highly elongated pore structure.
Titulo: In Situ Foaming of Porous (La0.6Sr0.4)0.98 (Co0.2 Fe0.8) O3-δ (LSCF) Cathodes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Applications
